New Records: Anrich Nortje is now his nation's leading wicket-taker in a men's T20 World Cup, with 31 wickets.
Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock scored 65 runs against England.
David Miller hit 43 off 28 balls, departing at the start of the final over.
Ottneil Baartman was hit for 21 runs in the 17th over.
Kagiso Rabada removed Liam Livingstone two balls into the 18th over.
